-- Intesa to sell equity stakes by 2017 - CEO 
-- By Silvia Aloisi
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 08:40AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, March 28 (Reuters) - Italy's Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> will in the next three years sell its stakes in airline Alitalia, Telecom Italia's <TLIT.MI> holding company Telco and publisher RCS Mediagroup <RCSM.MI>

"We will sell all our equity holdings by 2017. Fullstop," Intesa CEO Carlo Messina told reporters on Friday.